Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Roughly chop @spinach{5%ounce}(roughly chopped). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered). Thinly slice
each @demi-baguette{2}(thinly sliced) into 8-10 pieces. Dice @tomato{2}(diced) into 1/4-inch pieces. Mince @chives{1/4%ounce}(minced).

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium heat. Add spinach to hot pan.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Reduce heat to medium low. Stir in @Vidalia onion paste{1/2%ounce}, @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce}, and 1/2 cup water.
Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @cream cheese{4%tablespoon} to pan and stir until melted. Remove from heat.

Stir in @ricotta cheese{8%ounce} and juice from two lemon wedges. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Let sit until
cooled slightly, ~{5%minutes}.

While filling cools, halve @fresh lasagna noodles{10%ounce}(halved widthwise) widthwise (you'll make 10 smaller noodles).

Spread 1/2 cup @marinara sauce{1} in a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{}.

Place one noodle on a work surface with a short side facing you; spread with 2 heaping tablespoons filling, leaving a
1/2-inch border. Starting with a short side, gently roll up (don't roll too tightly; filling might come out the sides!).

Place roll-up, seam side down, on top of marinara in baking dish. Repeat assembly with remaining noodles and filling.

Pour remaining marinara evenly over roll-ups, spreading to cover. Sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}(shredded).

Tightly cover #baking dish{} with #foil{}; bake on top rack for ~{20%minutes}.

Carefully remove foil. Return to top rack and bake until cheese begins to brown and noodles are tender,
~{5-8%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, place baguette slices on a #baking sheet{}. Top with a large drizzle of olive oil and season with salt and
pepper. Bake on middle rack until lightly browned and toasted, ~{5-8%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomatoes, chives, lemon zest, and juice from remaining lemon wedges. Season with salt and pepper.

Top crostini with tomato mixture.

Serve lasagna roll-ups family style or divide between plates. Serve with tomato crostini on the side.

> For 8 servings, you may need to work in batches when cooking the spinach, and bake on top and middle racks.
> The zucchini in the original recipe is replaced by Vidalia onion paste here - you can substitute with 1/2 cup grated zucchini if desired.
> This recipe is double the typical servings, providing 4 servings and 8 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.